The impeachment trial of President Trump has ended, but the threat to our democracy continues.
President Trump’s actions demonstrate the need to develop and pass legislative reforms to safeguard the checks and balances of our democracy.
As a result, the career prosecutors on the case demonstrated something in short supply in the White House but abundant among public servants — moral courage.
One first step was introduced by my fellow House impeachment manager, Hakeem Jeffries, to require logging and disclosure of White House contacts with DOJ.
President Trump has repeatedly dangled pardons to his associates as they face federal criminal investigations.